I tried brute-forcing itâ€¦ It took a while to fully figure out what I wanted to do, but the idea behind just making a giant equation then solving for humn was there early on. I started by expanding the input by replacing monkeys with their value if they had one or operation if they didnâ€™t. I then replaced all the monkeys with their values, just like in Part 1. This left me with a giant expression where the only variable was humn. I just wasnâ€™t sure how to actually solve equations in R so I kept trying to brute-force it, which kept on not working. I eventually found the Ryacas package which made quick work of everything.

